The paper deals with regular languages and their difference hierarchies, which are topics in formal language theory (cs.FL) and combinatorics (cs.DM). The techniques used in the paper involve set theory and logic, which are also relevant to the sub-categories of cs.LO (logic in computer science) and cs.CC (computational complexity). Finally, the paper also discusses polynomial closures of group languages, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT).
